  <description type="morphology">Stems erect, 25 mm.  Leaves 3–6.5 mm; laminal cells 10–25 µm, walls thin; basal cells long-rectangular, 140 µm, walls weakly thickened, smooth; basal marginal cells weakly differentiated, longer than laminal cells.  Seta 20–40 mm.  Capsule ovoid-cylindric, 2–3  mm, ribbed, exothecial cells long-rectangular, walls weakly thickened; peristome teeth linear, 1 mm, papillose, erect when wet, somewhat recurved or twisted when dry; endostome almost as long as teeth.  Operculum 2 mm.  Calyptra campanulate, 4–8 mm, smooth.  Spores 12–20 µm, papillose, brownish green.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Calcareous soils along stream and river banks in Arctic and montane habitats;</description>
